{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"imageBlock","attrs":{"src":"/assets/55435fdc-6cc3-4929-b863-818315b7b37f","alt":"Applying Boundary Constraints","caption":"","type":"url"}},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When optimizing functions using the Firefly algorithm, it is crucial to keep your fireflies within a valid search space. This guide shows you how to apply boundary constraints (clamping) to your fireflies and how to set up standardized testing environments to evaluate their performance."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Position Clamping Mechanism"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without boundaries, fireflies might wander off into invalid regions of your search space. To prevent this, we use a technique called "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"clamping"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Whenever a firefly calculates its new position, the algorithm checks if that position exceeds the defined boundaries. If it does, the firefly is placed exactly on the boundary edge."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is how you can implement position clamping in your update loop using Python and NumPy:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np

# Apply clamping during each update step
if bounds is not None:
    for d in range(len(new_pos)):
        # Clip the position to stay within the (min, max) bounds for this dimension
        new_pos[d] = np.clip(new_pos[d], bounds[d][0], bounds[d][1])"}]},{"type":"infoBlock","attrs":{"id":"info-1776710161407-kt7vco32j","type":"tip"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ensure your "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"bounds"},{"type":"text","text":" variable is structured as a list or array of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"(min, max)"},{"type":"text","text":" pairs for each dimension. For example, a 2D space bounded between -5 and 5 would be "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"[(-5, 5), (-5, 5)]"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How the Update Flow Works"}]},{"type":"mermaidBlock","attrs":{"id":"mermaid-1776710161407-hwhy9vrrg","diagram":"flowchart TD
    A[Calculate New Firefly Position] --> B{Are bounds defined?}
    B -- Yes --> C["Apply np.clip() to each dimension"]
