    D --> E","title":""}},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting Up Testing Environments"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To ensure your algorithm is working correctly, it's best to test it against standard mathematical benchmark functions before applying it to your real-world problem."}]},{"type":"stepsBlock","attrs":{"id":"steps-1776710161407-uecogmwps"},"content":[{"type":"stepBlock","attrs":{"title":"Configure your population"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For standard 2D testing, initialize a population of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"40 fireflies"},{"type":"text","text":" and set the algorithm to run for "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"100 iterations"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"stepBlock","attrs":{"title":"Select a benchmark function"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Choose a standard optimization function. We recommend starting with simple 2D functions to visualize the fireflies' behavior easily."}]}]},{"type":"stepBlock","attrs":{"title":"Set your parameters"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define your randomization parameter ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\alpha"}},{"type":"text","text":"), attractiveness at distance zero ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\beta_0"}},{"type":"text","text":"), and light absorption coefficient ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"\gamma"}},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]}]},{"type":"accordionBlock","attrs":{"id":"accordion-1776710161407-9sqaknrk7","multiple":true},"content":[{"type":"accordionTab","attrs":{"header":"View recommended 2D benchmark functions","icon":null,"disabled":false,"isActive":false},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The following functions are standard for visualizing and testing Firefly optimization in 2 dimensions:"}]},{"type":